  "text": "Click, tonal, or chirp type stimulus can be used in auditory brainstem response (ABR) measurements. [CITATION_1] Click stimulus is widely used in ABR measurements. However, the responses obtained using click stimulus are not from the whole cochlea, but are rather thought to originate from basal regions (2-4 kHz). [CITATION_2] Therefore, the chirp stimulus was developed to stimulate the entire cochlea simultaneously and provide effective neural synchronisation.",
